The mechanics of a common mezzanine card (CMC) family are defined in this standard. Mezzanine cards, designed to this standard, can be used interchangeably on VME, VME64 and VME64x boards, CompactPCI/sup (R)/ boards, Multibus/sup (R)/ I and II boards, desktop computers, portable computers, servers, and other similar types of applications. Mezzanine cards can provide modular front panel I/O, backplane I/O or general function expansion or a combination for host computers. Single, wide mezzanine cards are 75 mm wide by 150 mm deep by 8.2 mm high.